equation_narrative.headline: Polar context and Q-specific prediction channels drive confident glutamine selection
equation_narrative.story: The model assembles a polar, surface-exposed context through layers 1-23, reading 8 structural contacts and local sequence features. The representation remains diffuse through mid-layers, with the logit lens reflecting mixed hydrophobic and polar character as the model integrates information. At layer 24, Q-specific prediction channels activate sharply, and by layer 29, Q dominates at 41.5% probability. Strong Q-specific MLP neurons in layers 25-30 and high-enrichment SAE features in layer 30 drive the final 99.55% confidence prediction.

perception_phase.summary: Layers 1-23 assemble a polar, surface-exposed context. The model reads 8 structural contacts through attention heads, with early layers showing mixed signals. The logit lens trajectory is volatile, with the representation character shifting from small/flexible residues (S, G, A dominate L1-8) to aromatic/polar (Y, H appear L2-16) to hydrophobic (V peaks at 33.8% at L22). This volatility reflects the model integrating diverse local and structural information rather than committing to predictions. Key features at L9 (F9:5728, F9:1281) and L18 (F18:7701, F18:9398) encode positional and secondary structure context. No co-evolutionary signal is present, indicating this position is not functionally coupled to distant residues.
perception_phase.context_character: By layer 23, the representation encodes a polar, surface-exposed position in a flexible loop region. The local sequence context (IPPDQ[Q]RLIFA) is polar-rich with charged neighbors (D40, R42), and the 8 structural contacts provide mixed chemistry without strong hydrophobic burial constraints.
key_information_sources: Structural contacts: 8 residues within 8Å, read primarily through attention heads at L28 (head 10, 1.604 proj) and L31 (head 14, 1.515 proj)
Local sequence: Strong polar context from D40 and R42 neighbors, integrated through local attention at L30 (head 15, -2.627 eraser) and L31 (head 3, 1.524 writer)
L9 features: F9:5728 (57.52 proj) and F9:1281 (52.15 proj) encode positional and secondary structure context
L18 features: F18:7701 (26.75 proj) and F18:9398 (26.3 proj) refine structural environment encoding

decision_phase.summary: The decision crystallizes at layer 24, where Q-specific prediction channels first activate (Q rises from 6.98% at L23 to 15.4% at L24). Layer 25 brings strong Q-specific MLP neurons (N25:4354 contributes 1.181 proj), and layers 28-30 see massive Q support from both attention and MLP streams. By layer 29, Q reaches 41.5% and then surges to 99.55% by layer 33, driven by high-enrichment SAE features (F30:2, F30:3571) and decisive MLP neurons (N30:2658, N30:5046).
decision_phase.transition: The L23-25 boundary marks the shift from perception to decision. At L23, the representation is diffuse (C leads at 14.0%, but no candidate exceeds 22%). At L24, Q-specific features activate (F24:5691 with 27.98 proj), and MLP neurons begin casting real votes for Q (N24:2554, N24:1907, N24:226 collectively contribute 1.68 proj). This is when the representation transitions from encoding 'what's here' to committing to 'Q should go here.'

candidates.narrative: Q emerges decisively at layer 24 (15.4%) and rises steadily through the decision phase, reaching 41.5% at L29 and 99.55% at L33. The strongest support comes from L25 MLP neuron N25:4354 (1.181 proj, Q-specific), L30 SAE features F30:2 (29.14 proj) and F30:3571 (25.9 proj), and L33 features F33:6423 (105.46 proj) and F33:3289 (97.75 proj). The model's confidence reflects strong alignment between the polar local context and Q's amide side chain chemistry.
candidates.key_layers: Emerges at L24, dominant by L29, overwhelming by L33
key_evidence: N25:4354 (1.181 proj) — Q-specific MLP neuron with strongest single contribution
F30:2 (MLP, 29.14 proj) — high-activation Q prediction channel
F33:6423 (attn, 105.46 proj) — final-layer Q commitment feature
N30:2658 (0.592 proj) and N30:5046 (0.508 proj) — late MLP support

candidates.narrative: E peaks very early at layer 3 (12.13%) when the representation is still encoding charged/polar character from the local context. It fades rapidly after L8 (2.36%) and remains below 1% throughout the decision phase, finishing at 0.12%. E's early prominence in the logit lens reflects the model reading the charged neighbor D40, but E-specific prediction channels never activate in layers 24+.
candidates.key_layers: Peaks at L3, fades by L8, irrelevant after L23
key_evidence: Early logit lens peak (12.13% at L3) reflects charged context encoding, not prediction
No significant E-specific MLP neurons or SAE features in decision layers
Erased by N24:858 (-0.458 proj, votes against E with 1.095 proj)

candidates.narrative: L shows a surprising late surge, peaking at 25.07% at layer 28 before collapsing to 0.09% by L33. This transient spike is driven by hydrophobic MLP neurons at L28-29 that briefly push toward hydrophobic residues before Q-specific channels overwhelm them. L's trajectory illustrates the model exploring hydrophobic alternatives before committing to the polar answer.

candidates.narrative: V dominates the logit lens from L14-22, peaking at 33.8% at L22. This reflects the model's representation being consistent with small, hydrophobic residues during the mid-perception phase as it integrates structural contacts. V is not a serious prediction candidate — it never activates V-specific prediction channels in layers 24+, and its logit lens prominence is purely a representation artifact.

Erased by N24:2680 (-0.479 proj) and N24:1565 (-0.478 proj) at decision onset

turning_points.description: The perception-to-decision transition occurs here. At L23, the representation is diffuse and hydrophobic-leaning (C leads at 14.0%, V at 13.2%). Layer 24 brings the first Q-specific prediction channels (F24:5691 with 27.98 proj) and MLP neurons that vote specifically for Q (N24:2554, N24:1907, N24:226 contribute net 2.12 proj). By L25, Q-specific neuron N25:4354 fires with 1.181 proj, and Q rises to 18.7%. This is when the model stops encoding context and starts committing to an answer.

The decisive surge occurs here. L28 sees strong structural attention (head 10, 1.604 proj) and a transient hydrophobic spike (L and M peak at 25.07% and 21.25%). But L29-30 bring overwhelming Q support: N29:1239 (0.778 proj), N29:4776 (0.753 proj), and L30 SAE features F30:2 (29.14 proj) and F30:3571 (25.9 proj) all fire strongly for Q. Q jumps from 26.4% at L27 to 41.5% at L29, and hydrophobic alternatives collapse. This is where the model's confidence crystallizes.

Final commitment and confidence refinement. L31-32 see massive MLP activity (net -8.23 proj at L31, -2.97 at L32) that erases remaining alternatives. L33 features F33:6423 (105.46 proj), F33:3289 (97.75 proj), and F33:9048 (95.33 proj) provide overwhelming Q support, driving the final 99.55% confidence. The model has fully committed, and these final layers refine the logit distribution to near-certainty.

deep_dives.label: Structural attention L28-31
deep_dives.caption: L28 head 10 (1.604 proj) and L31 head 14 (1.515 proj) read structural contacts and write strongly for Q. These heads integrate 3D neighbor chemistry into the decision. L31 head 3 (1.524 proj) focuses on local sequence context (D40, R42).

deep_dives.label: Decision onset: MLP L24-26
deep_dives.caption: L24-25 mark the transition to decision. N24:2554, N24:1907, N24:226 cast the first Q-specific votes (net 2.12 proj). N25:4354 (1.181 proj) is the strongest single Q-specific neuron in the entire network. L26 shows mixed activity (net -3.73 proj) as the model explores alternatives before committing.

deep_dives.label: Q prediction channels at L30
deep_dives.caption: L30 features F30:2 (29.14 proj), F30:3571 (25.9 proj), F30:2288 (25.53 proj), and F30:6682 (25.2 proj) are high-activation Q prediction channels. These MLP-stream features encode Q-specific patterns and drive the L29-30 surge from 41.5% to final confidence.

deep_dives.label: Confidence surge: MLP L29-31
deep_dives.caption: L29-31 see the decisive Q surge and alternative erasure. N29:1239 (0.778 proj) and N29:4776 (0.753 proj) support Q. N30:4717 (-0.992 proj) erases hydrophobic alternatives (V, I). N31 shows massive activity (net -8.23 proj) that collapses all non-Q candidates.

deep_dives.label: Final commitment at L33
deep_dives.caption: L33 features provide overwhelming Q support: F33:6423 (105.46 proj), F33:3289 (97.75 proj), F33:9048 (95.33 proj), F33:3601 (94.7 proj). These final-layer features encode absolute Q commitment and drive the 99.55% confidence.

deep_dives.label: Early context assembly L1-9
deep_dives.caption: L1 features encode raw sequence context. L9 features (F9:5728, F9:1281, F9:2619) encode positional and secondary structure information. The logit lens shows mixed signals (S, G, A, E) reflecting diverse context integration, not prediction attempts.

equation_narrative.resolution: The model correctly predicts Q with 99.55% confidence by assembling a polar, surface-exposed context through layers 1-23 and activating Q-specific prediction channels in layers 24-33. The decisive evidence is the convergence of structural attention (L28 head 10, L31 head 14), Q-specific MLP neurons (N25:4354, N29:4776, N30:5046), and high-enrichment SAE features (F30:2, F33:6423). The local sequence context (D40, R42 neighbors) and lack of hydrophobic burial constraints align perfectly with Q's polar amide side chain, and the model's confidence reflects this strong biochemical coherence.
